.intro
  %p Below are four Carousel objects created from the same Carousel class.  Basic features are as follows:
  %ul 
    %li Viewing size is 400x300 pixels
    %li Navigation arrows appear at side edges on hover
    %li Download is on lower-right corner
    %li Pause/unpause on middle hover
    %li Fetches JSON via AJAX
    %li Wraps around
    %li Auto-sliding direction follows the last navigation arrow pressed (i.e., if you pressed the left arrow, the carousel will auto-slide towards the left.)
    %li Default transition time for auto-slide is 1800ms

#carouselA
%p 
  %b Default Carousel
  %br
  This carousel uses all basic features mentioned.  All images are 400x300 in size.


#carouselB
%p 
  %b Support for User-configured Options 
  %br
  User-configured options shown above are: viewing size (600x200), Background-color (pink), &  Transition time (3000ms). All images are 400x300 in size.

#carouselC
%p 
  %b Support for all Image Sizes and a Portrait Viewport.
  %br
  All image sizes are supported; and if the image is too small, its natural resolution is preserved. Viewing size is 300x500 (portrait). Background-color is of a green hue.


#carouselD
%p 
  %b Support for Flickr API using JSONP
  %br
  Flickr API was used with the keyword 'dog' to fetch the images, and the data was in JSONP instead of JSON.  Background-color is of a blue hue.


